


         Throw                                                          Throws
  1. Throw is used to throw the exception                    1. to declare exception
  2. Throw is used in the method signature                   2. with method signature
  3. Throw is followed by instance/object                    3. throws is followed by class
  4. Throw can not be used with multiple Exception           4. we can declare multiple exception



  lifecycle of thread

   new state()       new =>       when you create object of thread and before invocation of start().
   Runnable()        runnable =>  when start method is invoked but thread scheduler is not selected as running thread
   Running ()         running =>  when thread scheduler is selected as running thread.
  Blocking()/WAit()   Blocking => when thread is waiting or sleep that time thread is in blocking state
  Dead()              died =>     after exit of run method